==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heritage
<hw>Her"it*age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>heritage</ets>, <ets>eritage</ets>, OF. <ets>heritage</ets>,
<ets>eritage</ets>, F. <ets>h⟦eacute⟧ritage</ets>, fr.
<ets>h⟦eacute⟧riter</ets> to inherit, LL. <ets>heriditare</ets>. See
<er>Hereditable</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That which is inherited,
or passes from heir to heir; inheritance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Part of my <qex>heritage</qex>,⟦br⟧
Which my dead father did bequeath to me.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Script.)</fld> <def>A possession; the Israelites,
as God's chosen people; also, a flock under pastoral charge.</def>
<rj><au>Joel iii. 2.</au> <au>1 Peter v. 3.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heritance</ent>⟦br⟧
